cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE. 

This paper deals with the complexity of XPath containment, which is a problem related to querying and searching data in databases and information systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of variables and their semantics, which is a topic related to programming languages and semantics, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely sub-category. The use of disjunction and the investigation of containment relative to a given DTD suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the study of complexity and algorithms, which is a topic related to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category as well.
